    dc:creator "Minghetti, Eugenia; Montemayor, Sara Itzel; Dellape, Pablo Matias" ;
    dc:date "2024" ;
    dc:title "Two new genera and four new species of Neotropical Eccritotarsini (Heteroptera, Miridae, Bryocorinae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.71.104130.figure1>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.71.104130.figure2>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.71.104130.figure3>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.71.104130.figure11> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.71.104130.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Thomasomiris gen. nov. and Egerocoris gen. nov. new species, dorsal habitus and labels. A. T. setosus sp. nov., female holotype; B. E. dimorphus sp. nov., male holotype; C. E. ecuatorianus sp. nov., male holotype; D. E. chaparensis sp. nov., male holotype." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/963755" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.71.104130.figure2>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Thomasomiris gen. nov. and Egerocoris gen. nov. new species, head frontal view. A. T. setosus sp. nov., female holotype; B. E. dimorphus sp. nov., male holotype; C. E. ecuatorianus sp. nov., male holotype; D. E. chaparensis sp. nov., male holotype." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/963756" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.71.104130.figure3>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Thomasomiris gen. nov. and Egerocoris gen. nov. new species, head and pronotum lateral view. A. T. setosus sp. nov., female holotype; B. E. dimorphus sp. nov., male holotype; C. E. ecuatorianus sp. nov., male holotype; D. E. chaparensis sp. nov., male holotype." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/963757" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.71.104130.figure11>
    dc:description "Figure 11. Distributional map of the species included in the genera Thomasomiris gen. nov. and Egerocoris gen. nov. Blue dot represents occurrence of Thomasomiris setosus sp. nov.; yellow dots represent occurrences of Egerocoris dimorphus sp. nov.; orange dot represents ocurrence of E. ecuatorianus sp. nov.; in grey the province Chapare (Bolivia) where E. chaparensis sp. nov. occurs." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/963765" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

